<div id="centering-tab-content" class="tab-content">
  <p>Centering things used to be one of the notoriously difficult things to do in CSS. With flexbox, we can now easily center elements 
    (both horizontally and vertically!)</p>

  <div class="centering-box">
    <button>Meet me in the middle</button>
  </div>

  <p>This is achieved by setting the following properties on the container's class:</p>

  <pre>
  .centering-box {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center; /* Centers content vertically */
    justify-content: center; /* Centers content horizontally */
  }</pre>
